FBIS3-17600 "drsov059_b_94026" FBIS-SOV-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Polls Show Belief in Possible Communist Return LD2603175494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1347 GMT 26 Mar 94 LD2603175494 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] More and more citizens of Russia believe that the return to the communist past is possible, an opinion poll taken by the All-Russian Center of Public Opinion Studies (VCIOM) among 3,901 residents of cities and villages of the Russian Federation in mid- March shows. Thus, according to the data provided by VCIOM to INTERFAX, to the question "Will the Communist Party be able to become a real political force in Russia in future?" in May 1993 15 percent said "yes", in March 1994 -- 22 percent. The negative answer was given by 59 percent in May, and in March -- 45 percent. Those who found it difficult to answer were respectively 26 and 38 percent. The respondents were also asked: "Will the Communist Party be able to return to power in future?" These are the answers: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |May 1993 |March 1994 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Yes |11 |17 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |No |62 |45 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Undecided |27 |38 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Of those who consider the Communist party's return to power possible, half announced themselves supporters of a market reform. Experts believe that they do not favor the restoration of the old regime.
